     * The starred beamlines belong to the NIH-funded National Research
     Resource: Macromolecular Crystallography at the National Synchrotron
     Light Source

     1. X-Ray photons per second through a 200µm aperture, 300mA, 2.6GeV,
     = 1Å

     2. Q4 = Quantum-4 four-module CCD-based detector from Area Detector
     Systems Corp., B4 = four-module CCD-based detector from Phillips'
     group at Brandeis U., B1, B1.2 = one-module detectors from Brandeis

     3. PX = Protein and virus crystallography, MAD = Multiwavelength
     Anomalous Diffraction phasing methods, XAS = X-ray Absorption
     Spectroscopy, SAXS = small-angle scattering and diffraction, EXAFS =
     Extended X-ray Absorption Fine Structure
